		<div class="courseListDescription">This course introduces students to computer programming as a way of producing artworks, both still and moving, in 2 and 3 dimensions. Using the Processing programming language, students will develop software for generating and manipulating images and 3-dimensional objects in work that functions independently as well as in interactive contexts. This course places equal emphasis on technical work (code) and visual outcomes. No prior coding experience is required.</div>
	
	
