    <a href="/content/ryerson/calendar/2020-2021/courses/media-studies/FPN/700.html" title="FPN 700 - Visual Effects for Film II" class="courseListCourseLink"><span class="courseListCourseCode">FPN 700</span> - <span class="courseListCourseName">Visual Effects for Film II</span></a>
    
	
		<div class="courseListDescription">This is an advanced-level professional elective providing an exploration of contemporary visual effects techniques. Emphasis will be placed on the aesthetics and creation of successful visual effects. The history of visual effects and classic optical techniques will be covered as well as current digital techniques. Students will work individually and in groups to produce completed visual effects (VFX) shots and scenes. Students are required to have a working knowledge of compositing software prior to taking this course.</div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListLength"><span class="courseInfoLabels">Weekly Contact: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">Lab: 3 hrs. </span></div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListWeight"><span class="courseInfoLabels">GPA weight: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">1.00</span></div>
	
	
