    <a href="/content/ryerson/calendar/2020-2021/courses/media-studies/NPF/530.html" title="NPF 530 - Electronic and Digital Art" class="courseListCourseLink"><span class="courseListCourseCode">NPF 530</span> - <span class="courseListCourseName">Electronic and Digital Art</span></a>
    
	
		<div class="courseListDescription">This course provides an in-depth study of the emergence of electronic and digital art in the last half of the twentieth century and their development to the present. Movements, techniques and genres that will be explored include net art, code-based art, generative art, interactive media, interactive installation, virtual reality, augmented reality, robotics, animatronics, 3D printing, digital fabrication, post-internet art and issues related to digital preservation.</div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListLength"><span class="courseInfoLabels">Weekly Contact: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">Lecture: 3 hrs. </span></div>
	
	
