    <a href="/content/ryerson/calendar/2020-2021/courses/media-studies/NPF/549.html" title="NPF 549 - History of Photojournalism" class="courseListCourseLink"><span class="courseListCourseCode">NPF 549</span> - <span class="courseListCourseName">History of Photojournalism</span></a>
    
	
		<div class="courseListDescription">This course focuses on the production of press photographs, the work of the picture editor, the process of selection, the sequencing of photographs and creation of a visual story on the page as well as modes of dissemination. Using a historical approach, the course analyzes technical, cultural, sociological, economic, political and aesthetic aspects of press photographs, emphasizing the notion of indexicality and how the visual syntax of photographs influences the publication and reception of news.</div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListLength"><span class="courseInfoLabels">Weekly Contact: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">Lecture: 3 hrs. </span></div>
	
	
