    <a href="/content/ryerson/calendar/2020-2021/courses/media-studies/NPF/551.html" title="NPF 551 - Digital Media and Network Culture" class="courseListCourseLink"><span class="courseListCourseCode">NPF 551</span> - <span class="courseListCourseName">Digital Media and Network Culture</span></a>
    
	
		<div class="courseListDescription">This course explores the historic development of the internet and digital media looking at the social and political implications of network-based and digital technologies. Topics include net neutrality, privacy, surveillance, artificial intelligence, the preservation of digital content, and the political dimensions of technological design. It also considers new potentials that have emerged in terms of the networked distribution of art and media, the open source and free software movements, and the rise of citizen journalism.</div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListLength"><span class="courseInfoLabels">Weekly Contact: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">Lecture: 3 hrs. </span></div>
	
	
