    <a href="/content/ryerson/calendar/2020-2021/courses/media-studies/NPF/569.html" title="NPF 569 - Disaster Images: Memory and Response" class="courseListCourseLink"><span class="courseListCourseCode">NPF 569</span> - <span class="courseListCourseName">Disaster Images: Memory and Response</span></a>
    
	
		<div class="courseListDescription">This course will examine the creative response of visual artists, photographers, filmmakers and new media artists to disaster and social crisis. The work of creative practitioners will be shown to respond to crisis in modes not available to the fields of journalism or traditional documentary media. The course requires students to prepare short discussion papers and visual works on the themes of history, memory and disaster.</div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListLength"><span class="courseInfoLabels">Weekly Contact: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">Lecture: 3 hrs. </span></div>
	
	
