           <li class="courseListItem" style="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;padding:0 0 10px;list-style-image:none;list-style-type:none;">
           









  
    <a href="/content/ryerson/calendar/2020-2021/courses/media-studies/NPF/607.html" title="NPF 607 - Questions of Beauty" class="courseListCourseLink"><span class="courseListCourseCode">NPF 607</span> - <span class="courseListCourseName">Questions of Beauty</span></a>
    
	
		<div class="courseListDescription">The focus of this course will be the exploration of the resurgence of questions about the role of beauty in the postmodern era. While these questions have generally engaged the visual art world since the early 1990s they are not confined to it. Formative historical concepts as well as discussions around notions of beauty and related ideas such as the sublime and the abject in contemporary critical theory and artistic practice will be examined.</div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListLength"><span class="courseInfoLabels">Weekly Contact: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">Lecture: 3 hrs. </span></div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListWeight"><span class="courseInfoLabels">GPA weight: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">1.00</span></div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListUnits"><span class="courseInfoLabels">Billing Units: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">1</span></div>
	
    
